results.name: Number of partitions of n where every part appears at least 5 times.
link: R. H. Hardin, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..1000
maple: g := product(1+x^(5*j)/(1-x^j), j = 1..20): gser := series(g, x = 0, 80): seq(coeff(gser, x, n), n = 1..75); # _Emeric Deutsch_, Jun 28 2009
mathematica: nmax = 100; Rest[CoefficientList[Series[Product[1 + x^(5*k)/(1-x^k), {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x]] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Nov 28 2015 *)
